<strong><a title="PCHC‚Äôs New Website" href="/new-website/">Learn more about our new website here.</a></strong>";s:10:"post_title";s:29:"Announcing PCHC's New Website";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:28:"announcing-pchcs-new-website";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-10-21 12:40:46";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-10-21 16:40:46";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:26:"http://www.pchc.com/?p=944";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:12;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"968";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"5";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-09-24 10:38:33";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-09-24 14:38:33";s:12:"post_content";s:2033:"PCHC¬†is pleased to announce that Robert P. Allen MD, MHCM, FACC, Executive Medical Director has been named to Maine Health Management Coalition‚Äôs (MHMC) 20 in 20 list of influential health care leaders and is slated to receive the award at MHMC‚Äôs <a href="http://www.mehmc.org/symposium">Annual Symposium</a> on October 10<sup>th</sup>.¬†

¬†The contest, which opened in June of this year, was held in commemoration of Maine Health Management Coalition's 20th anniversary, and sought to recognize individuals from around the state that have made significant contributions to the Coalition's goals of improving population health, experience of care, and cost of health care services in Maine.¬† The winners were selected from a pool of applicants across the state and were judged by a panel of national health care improvement specialists.

¬†Kenneth Schmidt, MPA, PCHC President &amp; CEO, states, ‚ÄúDr. Bob Allen has been a phenomenal medical leader for seven years for PCHC. PCHC is a very different organization today than when he started with us.¬† PCHC is now nationally recognized for the comprehensiveness and quality of our integrated care, and is on the cutting edge of the health care transformation revolution in America. PCHC is the only accredited community health center in Maine (of 20), our seven family and pediatric practices have all achieved the highest level of national certification as Patient Centered Medical Homes, and we have tripled the number of providers to 200, staff to 700 and patients to almost 70,000 under Dr. Allen‚Äôs medical leadership.‚Äù

Robert P. Allen, MD, MHCM, FACC, has been with PCHC since 2006 and was previously with Northeast Cardiology Associates for 30 years. Dr. Allen has a Masters in Healthcare Management from Harvard.¬† He has served as President of the EMMC Medical Staff, Medical Director of EMMC Cardiac Wellness of Maine, Chief of Cardiology and Chief of Medicine of St. Joseph Hospital, and President of the Maine affiliate of the American Heart Association.";s:10:"post_title";s:51:"Dr. Robert Allen to Receive MHMC‚Äôs 20 in 20 Award";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:47:"dr-robert-allen-to-receive-mhmcs-20-in-20-award";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-09-30 10:46:54";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-09-30 14:46:54";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:26:"http://www.pchc.com/?p=968";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:13;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"971";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"5";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-09-27 10:42:25";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-09-27 14:42:25";s:12:"post_content";s:2757:"<h4>Consumers Encouraged to Enroll for Health Insurance Coverage</h4>
Penobscot Community Health Care (PCHC) and Maine Health Access Foundation (MeHAF) invite you to join the Bangor kickoff campaign to educate Maine people about the new Health Insurance Marketplace on the opening day of enrollment, October 1st.¬† Other kick-off events are being hosted in Lewiston, Portland, Presque Isle, and Waterville.¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†

As part of the Affordable Care Act, Health Insurance Marketplaces will be offering quality, affordable health care plans for Maine people.¬† Mainers are encouraged to visit <a href="http://www.healthcare.gov/">HealthCare.gov</a> to complete the streamlined application and enroll in a plan, <a href="http://www.enroll207.com/">enroll207.com</a> to learn more about the specific health insurance plans available to them, or the Kaiser Family Foundation Website to view a <a href="http://kff.org/health-reform/video/youtoons-obamacare-video/">video</a> about the Affordable Care Act and how the marketplace works.¬† The Maine Health Insurance Marketplace includes new health plans offered by Anthem Blue Cross and Blue Shield, as well as Maine‚Äôs new nonprofit health insurer, Maine Community Health Options.¬†

<strong>What:</strong> Health Insurance Marketplace Kick-Off Event

<strong>Where:</strong> PCHC Administrative Services Center, 103 Maine Avenue, Bangor

<strong>When:</strong> Tuesday, October 1<sup>st</sup> at Noon

Maine FQHCs received grant funding from the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) making it possible for health centers to assist the uninsured with enrolling in quality health coverage through the Health Insurance Marketplace.¬† PCHC‚Äôs Health Insurance Marketplace outreach and enrollment efforts will be led by Shawn Yardley, MS, Director of Community Services, who states, ‚ÄúPCHC is excited to be a resource to our patients and <em>anyone</em> needing health insurance. This is the long awaited opportunity allowing uninsured to access, through the Marketplace, essential health benefits including preventive and wellness services, chronic disease management, prescription drugs, behavioral health treatment, laboratory services, and 7 other key benefits. ‚Äú

PCHC will be working with MeHAF and the Center for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS), among others, to educate the public about the marketplace and encourage enrollment which runs October 1, 2013, through March 31, 2014.¬† <a href="http://wmca.org/health-care-reform/">Western Maine Community Action (WMCA)</a> and the <a href="http://fishingpartnership.org/">Maine Lobstermen‚Äôs Association</a> have trained certified assisters to help Maine people and small business understand and enroll in the new health plans.";s:10:"post_title";s:57:"Health Insurance Marketplace Opening Celebrated in Bangor";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:57:"health-insurance-marketplace-opening-celebrated-in-bangor";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-09-30 10:46:19";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-09-30 14:46:19";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:26:"http://www.pchc.com/?p=971";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:14;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"988";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"5";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-10-03 12:58:33";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-10-03 16:58:33";s:12:"post_content";s:1305:"Penobscot Community Health Care (PCHC) is pleased to announce that Peggy Clark, MA, CCC-SLP, has joined the staff of PCHC‚Äôs Warren Center to provide Speech Therapy Services.¬† Ms. Clark received her undergraduate degree from the University of Chattanooga, TN, and her Masters of Science in Communication from the University of Maine. ¬†Prior to joining Penobscot Community Health Care, Ms. Clark worked at West Texas Rehabilitation Center, San Angelo, TX, providing diagnosis and Treatment of pediatric, school, and adult speech disorders.¬† Robert Allen, MD, PCHC‚Äôs Executive Medical Director, states, ‚ÄúPeggy Clark, MA, CCC-SLP, is an excellent and highly experienced Speech Language Pathologist who is bringing back speech services to the Warren Center and patients of PCHC.¬† We are very fortunate to have her joining our staff.‚Äù¬† Ms. Clark has more than 15 years of experience as a Speech-Language Pathologist and is open to new patients; for an appointment please call 941-2850.¬† ¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†

¬†The Warren Center is located in a newly renovated space at 992 Union Street on PCHC's main campus in Bangor.¬† The Warren Center has been helping people of all ages overcome barriers to effective communication for over 50 years through speech therapy, audiology, and hearing aid services.";s:10:"post_title";s:61:"Peggy Clark, Speech-Language Pathologist, Joins Warren Center";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:59:"peggy-clark-speech-language-pathologist-joins-warren-center";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-10-03 12:58:33";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-10-03 16:58:33";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:26:"http://www.pchc.com/?p=988";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:15;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"1012";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"8";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-10-08 09:55:37";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-10-08 13:55:37";s:12:"post_content";s:1407:"Penobscot Community Health Care (PCHC) and St. Joseph Healthcare are hosting a Diabetes Expo on Friday, November 1<sup>st</sup> 9am-3pm at Jeff‚Äôs Catering in the East/West Industrial Park, 15 Littlefield Way, Brewer. The Diabetes Expo will feature special guest speaker and Diabetes Champion, <a href="http://www.pchc.com/image_upload/Charne-Ruth.pdf">Ruth Charne</a>, several area vendors and free giveaways, as well as a cooking demonstration and educational sessions on topics such as foot care, dental hygiene, and weight loss secrets.

