<b>¬†</b>Please join us for this day of workshops, exhibits and demonstrations on diabetes self-management techniques.¬† For more information, please contact Georgia Clark-Albert, PCHC Nutritionist and Diabetes Educator, at 941-2850.";s:10:"post_title";s:55:"PCHC & St. Joseph Healthcare to Host 2013 Diabetes Expo";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:49:"pchc-st-joseph-healthcare-host-2013-diabetes-expo";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-10-08 09:55:37";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-10-08 13:55:37";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://www.pchc.com/?p=1012";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:16;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"1016";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"8";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-10-10 14:11:25";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-10-10 18:11:25";s:12:"post_content";s:1783:"¬†Penobscot Community Health Care (PCHC) is pleased to announce that Lawrence Smith, MD, PCHC Community Care and Geriatrics Medical Director, has earned certification as Medical Director in Long Term Care from the Board of Directors of the American Medical Directors Certification Program (AMDCP).¬† The Certified Medical Director in Long Term Care Program was created to enhance the profession of medical direction throughout the long term care continuum and to reinforce the leadership role of the medical director in providing quality care. Dr. Smith currently oversees PCHCs Community Care and Geriatrics whose team of 20 clinicians provide care for many of the region's nursing homes, as well as medical care in assisted living facilities and homes.¬†

¬†Robert P. Allen MD, MHCM, FACC, Executive Medical Director, states, ‚ÄúPCHC is privileged to have Dr. Larry Smith among its leaders.¬† Dr. Smith has significant experience and is an expert in geriatric care.¬† His designation as a Certified Medical Director in Long Term Care is indicative of his commitment to quality care for PCHC patients.‚Äù¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†

¬†Dr. Smith received both his undergraduate degree and his Doctorate of Medicine from Ohio State University, followed by residency training at Eastern Maine Medical Center, and has been practicing since 1987.¬† Dr. Smith currently serves as Medical Director for a number of area nursing homes and was founder and lead family physician at Winterport Family Practice prior to joining Penobscot Community Health Care.¬† Dr. Smith is Board Certified by the American Academy of Family Physicians and is certified as a Medical Director by the American Medical Directors Association, in addition to being AMDCP Certified as Certified Medical Director in Long Term Care.";s:10:"post_title";s:67:"Lawrence Smith, MD, Certified as Medical Director In Long Term Care";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:59:"lawrence-smith-md-certified-medical-director-long-term-care";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-10-10 14:11:25";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-10-10 18:11:25";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://www.pchc.com/?p=1016";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:17;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"1040";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"8";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-10-16 09:04:38";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-10-16 13:04:38";s:12:"post_content";s:1817:"PCHC¬†is pleased to announce the addition of orthodontics to the range of services offered at PCHC Dental Center, 1048 Union Street, Bangor.¬† Very few offices in the state accept MaineCare for these services so it is especially important to PCHC‚Äôs mission and to patient access.

¬†To provide these services, PCHC has welcomed experience orthodontist, Edward Zanca, DMD, to its dental team.¬† Dr. Zanca received his undergraduate degree from the University of Maine, his Dental Medical Degree from Tufts University, completed a General Practice Residency Program at Maine Medical Center, as well as a Post Graduate Orthodontic Residency at Boston University School of Dental Medicine.¬† Dr. Zanca has been in private practice for more than 30 years.

¬†Philip Higgins, Jr., DMD, Chief Dental Officer, states ‚ÄúWe are pleased to offer orthodontics to patients who have found it difficult or impossible to obtain care that is so greatly needed. Dr. Zanca is a vastly experienced and competent orthodontist and his affiliation with PCHC will greatly enhance the services we can provide for our patients. He is widely respected in the orthodontic community and we are fortunate to add him to our list of competent dental providers. ‚Äù

¬†Dr. Zanca is accepting established patients of PCHC Dental Center for orthodontic services. For an appointment please call 207-945-5247, option 4.¬† MaineCare is accepted and services will fall under PCHC‚Äôs Affordable Care Program (Sliding fee scale) for those who qualify. PCHC has the largest public or private dental practice north of Boston, as well as Maine‚Äôs only Accredited Community General Practice Dental Residency and Accredited Pediatric Dental Residency.¬† In all, PCHC employs 24 fully licensed dentists, as well as about 15 registered dental hygienists.";s:10:"post_title";s:44:"PCHC Dental Center Now Offering Orthodontics";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:44:"pchc-dental-center-now-offering-orthodontics";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-10-16 09:04:38";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-10-16 13:04:38";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://www.pchc.com/?p=1040";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:18;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"1070";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"8";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-10-21 16:34:13";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-10-21 20:34:13";s:12:"post_content";s:1316:"Bangor, Maine - Penobscot Community Health Care (PCHC) is pleased to announce that Tina Brown, RN, MSN, FNP-C, has joined the medical staff of PCHC‚Äôs Penobscot Community Health Center, 1012 Union Street, Bangor.¬† Ms. Brown‚Äôs practice centers on all aspects of high-quality medical care, including patient physicals, acute visits, and health care maintenance.

Ms. Brown received her undergraduate degree from Husson University, her Masters of Science in Nursing from the University of Pheonix, Arizona, and a Certificate of Advanced Studies in Nursing from the University of Maine.¬† Prior to joining Penobscot Community Health Care, Ms. Brown provided skilled nursing home care for Genesis Healthcare.¬† Robert Allen, MD, PCHC‚Äôs Executive Medical Director, states, ‚ÄúPCHC welcomes Tina Brown, FNP, to her new practice at Penobscot Community Health Center on Union Street in Bangor.¬† Patients will find her to be very likeable, thoroughly competent, and will receive excellent care from her in primary care.‚Äù¬†

Ms. Brown is seeing patients at Penobscot Community Health Center; for an appointment please call 945-5247.¬† Penobscot Community Health Center is open seven days per week and, in addition to family medical care, offers Walk-In Care, Pharmacy, Physical Therapy, and Mental Health Services.";s:10:"post_title";s:58:"Tina Brown, FNP-C, Joins Penobscot Community Health Center";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:56:"tina-brown-fnp-c-joins-penobscot-community-health-center";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-10-21 16:34:13";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-10-21 20:34:13";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:23:"http://pchc.com/?p=1070";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:19;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"1098";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"5";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-10-23 15:34:24";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-10-23 19:34:24";s:12:"post_content";s:3349:"¬†The City of Bangor, the Bangor Area Homeless Shelter, Penobscot Community Health Care (PCHC), and numerous partner organizations are proud to work together for a collaborative community project, ‚ÄúPines‚Äù Clean Up, as part of the United Way of Eastern Maine‚Äôs Days of Caring, Friday, October 25, 2013.

¬†<b>Event Information</b>

<b>What:</b>¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† ‚ÄúPines‚Äù Clean Up

<b>When:</b>¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† October 25, 2013, 8:30 am

<b>Where:¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† </b>Volunteers will assemble at the Water Tower on Texas Avenue, Bangor.¬† General parking is available in a lot below the water tower.

¬†Clean up of the ‚ÄúPines‚Äù, a wooded area between Texas Avenue, Hammond Street and Interstate 95, is part of an on-going collaborative effort between the City of Bangor, Bangor Police Department, healthcare and social service organizations, and area homeless shelters to address public safety, the health and well-being of area citizens, and the quality of life in Bangor.

¬†Bangor Mayor Nelson Durgin said "This year's Bangor recognition of Days of Caring takes on special meaning as volunteers throughout the community come together to clean up the "Pines".¬† The Pines has been used for decades by homeless persons as an area to "camp out", and the evidence of alcohol abuse, and other substance abuse in this area has created a very unwelcoming plot in our city.¬† With leadership of the Bangor Public Works, Bangor Public Health and Community Services, The Bangor Homeless Shelter, PCHC/Hope House and the United Way, volunteers will enter the area and dispose of many years accumulation of unsightly and unhealthy trash.¬† All are welcome to participate and other participants will include volunteers from St. Joseph Hospital, Maine DOT and Sam's Club who will donate food which will be prepared for lunch by volunteers from the Job Corps.¬† Clearly, this will be a day of caring where these volunteers will really make a difference.‚Äù

Volunteers for the project are still needed!¬† Interested organizations or individuals may sign up at <a href="http://www.volunteermaine.org/">www.VolunteerMaine.org</a> or by calling the Bangor Area Homeless Shelter at (207)947-0092.¬† Volunteers are also welcome to meet at the Water Tower at 8:30 am on October 25.¬† General parking is available in a lot below the water tower.

¬†Volunteers should dress for outdoor weather, wear sturdy footwear (boots suggested) and bring heavy work gloves.¬† Lunch will be provided for all volunteers.¬† Food and drinks donated by Sam‚Äôs Club will be prepared at the Hope House kitchen and served by Penobscot Job Corps Academy students.

¬†Organizations volunteering time, resources and staff for event include:¬†
